# URL Auto Refresher + Agentic layer

**Product:** Chromium Manifest V3 **Edge extension** — scheduled tab refreshes, optional sync groups, jitter, focus-aware badge. **Plan / epics:** [doc/plan/EDGE_URL_AUTO_REFRESHER_PLAN.md](doc/plan/EDGE_URL_AUTO_REFRESHER_PLAN.md).

Cursor rules, skills, handoff protocol, and test discipline from [AgenticTemplate](https://github.com/pbuckles22/AgenticTemplate). Document your toolchain in AGENT_HANDOFF.md and TEST_PLAN.md.

Source of truth: PM_PLAN.md, AGENT_HANDOFF.md; .cursor/skills/ (DEV_GUIDE, TEST_TDD, DESIGN_SYSTEM, techwriter, tester, code-reviewer, tech-debt-evaluator, pm-governance, ui-ux, visual-match, chromium-mv3-extension, extension-architect, tech-lead, web-audio-dsp). **MV3 / messaging:** Before changing `manifest.json`, `src/background/`, content scripts (e.g. `src/content/page-overlay.ts`), or `src/lib/messages.ts`, read [.cursor/skills/chromium-mv3-extension/SKILL.md](.cursor/skills/chromium-mv3-extension/SKILL.md). **Skills by file context (not every edit):** When this session includes [.cursor/rules/skill-context-extension-architect.mdc](.cursor/rules/skill-context-extension-architect.mdc) or [.cursor/rules/skill-context-tech-lead.mdc](.cursor/rules/skill-context-tech-lead.mdc), follow those rules so architect / tech-lead / web-audio-dsp apply only where impact is high. Use techwriter for docs; use tester + .cursor/rules/testing.mdc for black-box tests. **TDD:** Read TEST_TDD.md and tester skill first; **Tier 1 (Vitest) and Tier 2 (Playwright)** use test-first before production code when that tier applies. **CI gate:** Before pushing to **`main`**, run **`npm run ci`** (tests + build + E2E); GitHub Actions runs the same on push (and on PRs if you open one).

**Handoff:** When the user wants a handoff, run code review (code-reviewer), tech debt (tech-debt-evaluator), and your project’s test/coverage commands as documented in AGENT_HANDOFF.md; record in the handoff note. See AGENT_HANDOFF.md and .cursor/rules/handoff-checklist.mdc — do not skip.
